  <summary date="2019-08-07T19:30:04Z" status="Introduced in House">Counter Terrorism and Illicit Finance Act 

This bill (1) increases the threshold dollar amounts above which financial institutions are required to file currency-transaction and suspicious-activity reports with the Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN), (2) directs FinCEN to establish a process for no-action letters, and (3) modifies other provisions related to&#160;anti-money laundering and counterterrorist financing.</summary>
